title: Shaun of the Dead
overview: A man's uneventful life is disrupted by the zombie apocalypse.

title: The Hangover
overview: Three buddies wake up from a bachelor party in Las Vegas, with no memory of the previous night and the bachelor missing. They make their way around the city in order to find their friend before his wedding.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

title: Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb
overview: An insane general triggers a path to nuclear holocaust that a War Room full of politicians and generals frantically tries to stop.

title: Birdman or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)
overview: A washed-up superhero actor attempts to revive his fading career by writing, directing, and starring in a Broadway production.

title: The Station Agent
overview: When his only friend dies, a man born with dwarfism moves to rural New Jersey to live a life of solitude, only to meet a chatty hot dog vendor and a woman dealing with her own personal loss.

title: The Shining
overview: A family heads to an isolated hotel for the winter where a sinister presence influences the father into violence, while his psychic son sees horrific forebodings from both past and future.

title: Me and Earl and the Dying Girl
overview: High schooler Greg, who spends most of his time making parodies of classic movies with his co-worker Earl, finds his outlook forever altered after befriending a classmate who has just been diagnosed with cancer.

title: The King of Comedy
overview: Rupert Pupkin is a passionate yet unsuccessful comic who craves nothing more than to be in the spotlight and to achieve this, he stalks and kidnaps his idol to take the spotlight for himself.

title: The Odd Couple
overview: Two friends try sharing an apartment, but their ideas of housekeeping and lifestyles are as different as night and day.

title: Invasion of the Body Snatchers
overview: A small-town doctor learns that the population of his community is being replaced by emotionless alien duplicates.

title: Peeping Tom
overview: A young man murders women, using a movie camera to film their dying expressions of terror.

title: Withnail & I
overview: In 1969, two substance-abusing, unemployed actors retreat to the countryside for a holiday that proves disastrous.

title: Sing Street
overview: A boy growing up in Dublin during the 1980s escapes his strained family life by starting a band to impress the mysterious girl he likes.

title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
overview: A distant poor relative of the Duke D'Ascoyne plots to inherit the title by murdering the eight other heirs who stand ahead of him in the line of succession.

title: The Breakfast Club
overview: Five high school students meet in Saturday detention and discover how they have a lot more in common than they thought.

title: Do the Right Thing
overview: On the hottest day of the year on a street in the Bedford-Stuyvesant section of Brooklyn, everyone's hate and bigotry smolders and builds until it explodes into violence.

title: Captain Fantastic
overview: In the forests of the Pacific Northwest, a father devoted to raising his six kids with a rigorous physical and intellectual education is forced to leave his paradise and enter the world, challenging his idea of what it means to be a parent.

title: The Royal Tenenbaums
overview: The eccentric members of a dysfunctional family reluctantly gather under the same roof for various reasons.

title: The Ladykillers
overview: Five oddball criminals planning a bank robbery rent rooms on a cul-de-sac from an octogenarian widow under the pretext that they are classical musicians.
